:{{A|VO vo ambient w4 v300 greeting enver 101.ogg}} {{A|VO vo ambient w4 v300 greeting enver 102.ogg}} '''Avilius:''' They say history tends to reflect the collective views of the past... and that's what worries me about the future. Regardless of the era, humans just can't seem to break free from the same mistakes.
:'''Avilius:''' But hey, don't stress too much. As long as there are Chrysos Heirs aiming to overthrow and become Titans, and there are still ordinary people like me pretending to be devout, Okhema's vibe won't be too suffocating... especially if they claim to worship {{Rubi|Thanatos|Death Titan}}.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} About the Golden Scapegoat...
:'''Avilius:''' ...Shh!
:'''Avilius:''' This is different from our usual banter. Let's go somewhere quieter to talk about this.
:'''Avilius:''' But... I guess you're the partner I've been waiting for. This is great news! Excellent news!
----
:'''Avilius:''' We can talk here.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Um, is this necessary?
::'''Avilius:''' Not really, but it's important enough to warrant a sense of seriousness!
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} I feel like I'm being robbed...
::'''Avilius:''' No way! You can take on ten of me easily!
:'''Avilius:''' Anyway, since you asked me about the Golden Scapegoat &mdash; a name that I came up with secretly &mdash; that means you've cleared the four basic stages as well, right?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} As well?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Oh, you mean...
:'''Avilius:''' Yes, I challenged them too, and was fortunate enough to pass the ones that weren't so dangerous. That's how I got this &mdash; the translations of the ancient Titan language that we can hear when the challenge starts or when the world is illuminated.
