:'''Avilius:''' Well? Feels like there's something... enigmatic behind it, right? For example... The dragonslayer inevitably becomes the evil dragon, and the torchbearer inevitably becomes ashes...
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} I have no idea.
::'''Avilius:''' That's true. Even the scholar who translated this couldn't be sure about it.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Really? She couldn't be sure about these misty poems?
::'''Avilius:''' Um...
::'''Avilius:''' Well, if it's the style that concerns you... just know that all of this is translated from the ancient Titan language, which I don't fully understand yet. Only the scholar knows if the original was also written in the same style.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} It's a little... How should I put it?
::'''Avilius:''' Right. It gives off an energy that's a little gloomy and deep... but extremely poetic!
:'''Avilius:''' Anyway, they're all precious information extracted and translated from the treasures bestowed upon us by the Golden Scapegoat, and I firmly believe that they are of unusual significance.
:'''Avilius:''' Just look at the first stanza. "Fire and light are the incarnation of that sin." Is this referring to the great Chrysos Heirs?
:'''Avilius:''' Maybe their plan to save the world will somehow cause irreversible damage to the world, but we must bear it no matter what? Are they hurting because of it, but are unable to explain anything to us mortals?
:'''Avilius:''' Also, in the second stanza, "After all, I know nothing of the butchering blade." The source of the information seems to believe that an unseen power from a mysterious domain is threatening the world... But what could it be?
:'''Avilius:''' Oh, and the last line of the fourth stanza... "The god wishes to see the world, and so {{Rubi|darkness|light}} came into being." The scholar was unable to precisely interpret the meaning of the Titan word here, and it contains two opposing interpretations. What does that mean?
:'''Avilius:''' ...Could it be that, in the ancient Titan language, light and darkness &mdash; Oh, and also time &mdash; are represented by the same word?
:'''Avilius:''' The scholar and I couldn't come up with any explanations that withstood scrutiny. Maybe the only way for us to answer it is to record more such whispers from the different challenges... But that might also bring about more questions!
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} What a conspiracy.
::'''Avilius:''' It is not a conspiracy! You're trying to conquer the Golden Scapegoat too, right? You can't possibly think that there are no surprising secrets within.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} I'm busy. Please just get to the point.
::'''Avilius:''' Basically, I think there's an incredible secret hidden in the Golden Scapegoat, but no one knows what it is, including me!
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Slow down... I can't keep up.
::'''Avilius:''' Um, did I speak too much?
:'''Avilius:''' ...Well, why don't I add you to our secret discussion group on the teleslate? Once you overcome more of the Golden Scapegoats, the scholar will be able to send her newer translations to the group.
:'''Avilius:''' It's much safer compared to meeting up in person frequently.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Ah, a secret investigation with a single point of contact!
::'''Avilius:''' Yes, you get it! It's more exciting if the research feels a little forbidden, right?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} ...Why can't we be more open about it?
::'''Avilius:''' I would like to, but the scholar specifically warned me that the research might be linked to the underlying rules of the world, and that we shouldn't talk about it openly before we make concrete discoveries...
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Whatever, I'm not interested.
::'''Avilius:''' Don't say that! You're here already, aren't you?
:'''Avilius:''' Anyway, people might start suspecting us if we stay here any longer. Let's talk on teleslate next time! Don't mention this conversation when I see you in Kephale Plaza!
